                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="rubrication" xml:id="d0">Nomina sacra; a few lines on the incipit page and fol. 7r, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of each section; names of Hebrew letters in Ps. 118 (e.g., fols. 35va, 37vb, 38vb); abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; some other words like, halle luya (e.g., fols. 5ra, 12va), ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 16ra, 17va), ʾǝgäle (e.g., fols. 18va, 28ra), wä-yǝbälu (e.g., fols. 24va, 25rb), kǝśtät (e.g., fols. 33vb, 50rb).</decoNote>
